# ACT III

## Scene I — The Palace

A room in the castle. Evening. The light is cool and dim.

LX (cue 45) [fade=5s]: Fade up from blackout — dim interior
SQ (cue 22) [file="wind_distant.wav", level=40%]: Distant wind ambience begins

OPHELIA moves slowly to center stage.

[[LX (cue 45a) [fade=8s]: Subtle shift — warmer on OPHELIA]]

KING
How fares our cousin Hamlet?

SQ (cue 23) [warn=10s]: Subtle underscore ready

HAMLET enters from upstage.

LX (cue 46) [fade=2s]: Isolate HAMLET in special — cool downlight

HAMLET
To be, or not to be, that is the question:
Whether 'tis nobler in the mind to suffer
The slings and arrows of outrageous fortune...

[[SQ (cue 23) on "To be" [fade=4s, level=25%]: Underscore begins — low and sparse]]

LX (cue 47) on "die" [fade=3s]: Shift — colder, more isolated

HAMLET (CONT'D)
To die, to sleep — no more.

SQ (cue 24) [warn=30s]: Thunder standby

OPHELIA
My lord...

LX (cue 48) [fade=2s]: Restore — warmer two-shot
SQ (cue 24) with "My lord" [file="thunder_distant.wav", level=60%]: Distant thunder roll
